news.title: GST not payable on house rented to proprietor for residential purpose: CBIC
news.para: ​The Central Board of Indirect Taxes and Customs (CBIC) also notified amendments in GST rates effective from January 1, 2023 for certain goods and services, as per the recommendations of the GST Council in its meeting on December 17.

news.title: Office space absorption in six cities touch 54.8 million sq ft in 2022: Savills India
news.para: Bengaluru recorded its all-time peak at 17.3 million sq ft; and so did NCR and Chennai at 11.3 million sq ft and 7.3 million sq ft respectively. New supply rose by 45.1% at 53.4 million sq ft when compared to 2021.

news.title: Bengaluru, Mumbai & Pune emerge as most searched cities for properties in 2022: Report
news.para: Magicbricks.com is owned by Magicbricks Realty Services, which is a subsidiary of Times Internet.

news.title: Glitches in Ahmedabad development body's portal stall realty launches; buyers hit too
news.para: With the portal being defunct for at least a month and a half, approvals related to realty projects are pending. These include building use permission (BU), construction plan clearances, and the approval of progress reports.

news.title: Telangana government's land bank to grow by 3,000 acre with SCB-GHMC merger
news.para: ​This will include Cantonment land, vacant land located within SCB properties like parks, service water reservoirs, gardens, SCB employees’ residential quarters, workshops and other land parcels where new projects were proposed to come up.

news.title: Property tax deadline ends on Dec 31, Suvidha centres to open in Ludhiana
news.para: ​According to MC records, more than 34,300 property owners in the city are yet to pay tax for the financial year 2022-23. Those who make the payment after Saturday will have to pay penalty.

news.title: New auction policy and illegal colonies' framework soon in Punjab
news.para: Arora said he recently took stock of the complaints received at Real Estate Regulatory Authority (Rera) – 3,500 in five years – and 85 % to 90 % of the complaints of the individual plot holders was that they were not given possession on time.

news.title: NGT seeks Telangana government's report on sports village violations
news.para: The NGT bench issued the orders after lake activist Lubna Sarwath filed a petition. It said the report will have to mention whether consent has been obtained from Pollution Control Board.

news.title: Prayagraj to get three more cement production units
news.para: At present the district has two cement plants running—a Cement blending plant of 6.6 million tonnes per annum (MTPA) of Jaypee Group at Sadwa and another of Ulta Tech Cement having a 2MTPA plant at Bara.

news.title: Dharavi's economic contribution to be kept in mind while redevelopment: Maharashtra Deputy CM
news.para: ​Dharavi, located in the central part of the country's financial capital and among the biggest slum clusters in the world, is a hub for several small-scale, unorganised industries that manufacture medicines, leather, footwear, clothes etc.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh government plans to set up 100 townships in five years
news.para: Out of the 29 development authorities in the state, the larger ones covering the urban areas of Lucknow, Kanpur, Prayagraj, Meerut, Agra, Varanasi, Ghaziabad, Gorakhpur, Meerut, Mathura, Moradabad and Bareilly will have to set up at least four townships, while the remaining have been given the task of establishing two.

news.title: Kolkata: Ambuja Neotia group buys 10-acre Nonadanga plot for Rs 260 crore
news.para: The starting bid price for the 10 acre land had been fixed at Rs 177.2 crore. The e-auction was conducted by the Housing Infrastructure Development Corporation (Hidco).

news.title: NCLT admits IDFC First's plea against Marvel Realtors
news.para: IDFC First Bank had sanctioned a term loan of ₹48 crore in favour of Marvel Realtors & Developers at an interest rate of 17.5% per annum in July 2017.

news.title: House prices in UK end 2022 on a weaker note after pandemic boom
news.para: The lender also said that the final month of 2022 saw prices record their worst run since 2008 on a monthly basis, falling 0.1% compared with November in their fourth consecutive monthly price fall.

news.title: Property registrations rise 9% in Mumbai during 2022 to 1.22 lakh units
news.para: Registration of properties stood at 64,242 units in 2013; 63,636 units in 2014; 67,400 units in 2015; 63,255 units in 2016; 68,659 units in 2017; 80,746 units in 2018; 67,863 units in 2019; and 65,633 units in 2020.
